        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug 19. 1877</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged for your letter with respect to Pontederia, as your information &amp; specimens will be very useful should another edition of my book be required.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Leggett’s letter has not been found, but see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10808.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. H. Leggett, 22 January 1877</ref> and n. 3. CD added a reference to Leggett’s published observations confirming tristyly in <hi rend="italic">Pontederia cordata</hi> to the preface to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9500.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. viii.</note>
